Using the solar array experimental platform presented above, we performed a series of experiments to determine the relationship between the panel inclination angles, inflow wind speed and convection heat transfer coefficient. Four inclination angles were chosen with respect to the main streamwise direction, representative of standard arrangements at different latitudes: [15°, 30°, 45°, −30°]. The negative inclination angle represents the same standard solar farm with 30° inclination for which the wind inflow is perpendicular to the back side of the panels. Figure 2 illustrates the flow field (normalized, ensemble-averaged velocity magnitude spatial contours and Reynolds shear stress) for the four inclination angles.Figure 2
